4. Why do we use lambda expressions in Java? 

• Conciseness: Reduces the boilerplate code required by anonymous inner classes. 
• Readability: Makes code easier to read by focusing on the logic rather than the structure. 
• Functional Programming: Enables the use of functional programming features, such as the Stream API. 

5. Is it mandatory for a lambda expression to have parameters?
No. If the abstract method in the functional interface takes no arguments, 
